I don’t use any delivery apps, and in order to save small restaurants the fee I always. place order by phone or in person. After attempting to call Xinh Xinh and not reaching anyone I drove to the location and stood waiting at the register for nearly 10 minutes without being acknowledged. I could see that they were busy so I stood waiting patiently. In that time I could see multiple new order alerts come through on their various delivery apps. When someone finally approached the counter they avoided eye contact or any greeting and instead proceeded to sort through all the new orders that arrived while I was waiting. I understand that restaurants rely heavily on delivery apps during that pandemic...but if that’s their priority, well...I wish them luck! Sad.

I drive up here from St. Louis to visit my sister and make sure to come here every time! I have yet to find comparable pho in St. Louis, despite the many Vietnamese restaurants here. I get the dac biet pho every time, and the broth is sooo flavorful! It's a challenge, but I try to drink all of the broth because it's so delicious. The portion is generous for the price, with plenty of noodles, meat, and sprouts/herbs.  Due to my love of the dac biet pho, I have not tried the other main dishes but I am sure they are delicious. The shrimp cake rolls are another of my favorites, and the deep fried eggs are an interesting but tasty appetizer.

A nice cafe with  good table service. We had the papaya salad and also the  Large combination rice noodles bowl with everything. It was a very good, came with bean sprouts and  a good portion of Thai basil leaves and lime.   Papaya salad had good seasoning, Although a bit too much sauce. Price is very reasonable. It came to 30 for 2 bowls of noodles and  papaya  salad.

(Note that they’re open on Sundays from 11-4 but Google doesn’t reflect this)  The pho is sooooooooooo amazing, best I’ve ever had! The broth is so rich and flavorful, this is the first place where I drank all the broth after finishing eating the solids even tho I was so full because the broth is so delicious. The meat portions are generous as well as the sprouts and garnishes that come with.  My sister and I both got combo pho (with no tendon but that’s just personal preference, it’s probably delicious for people who like tendon) twice in the span of less than 24 hours. The prices are absolutely amazing, $9 for an enormous bowl of pho. We also got the Thai iced tea which is fantastic too. The service was great, and the menu has a great selection of apps and drinks and food besides pho (but seriously, get the pho).  Definitely come here and support this awesome place!
